There seems to be some issue with the way this plays with `--check-untyped-defs`, see [this playground example](https://mypy-play.net/?mypy=latest&python=3.11&flags=check-untyped-defs&gist=6a2e49ffa6670369246e11fcecac37e2):

```python
from typing_extensions import override

class A:
    def f(self, x: int) -> int:
        return 2

class B(A):
    
    @override
    def f(self, x: int): # why `-> int` is not inferred?
        return None # why return type violation is not reported?
    
    @override
    def g(self, y): # why "no base method" is not reported?
        return 4
```
